ZCZC GE34
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 082300 UTC
DURING MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY THE AZORES HIGH WILL EXTEND A RIDGE NWARDS
TO CONNECT TO A HIGH PRESSURE NEAR ICELAND. LOW PRESSURE 1005 OVER GERMANY
DURING MONDAY EVENING WILL GRADUALLY EXTEND A LOW PRESSURE TROUGH NWARDS
AND WWARDS TO LIE NEAR NORMANDY AND SERN ENGLAND BY LATE TUESDAY AND EARLY
WEDNESDAY. ON WEDNESDAY THE LOW PRESSURE CENTRES WILL MOV SLTLY FURTHER N
ON A LINE WALES TO THE N SEA WHILE THE HIGH PRESSURE MOVS SLTLY W OF ICELAND.
A SIMILAR PRESSURE PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH THURSDAY WITH A DPN LOW
PRESSURE CENTRE 997 NEAR EERN ENGLAND. DURING MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY
WINDS WILL BECOME NE AND STRENGTHEN IN THE N SEA WITH GALES POSS IN TYNE
DOGGER AND HUMBER FOR A TIME AND POSSIBLY FORTIES AND FORTH LATER. DURING
WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY STRG WINDS WILL CONTINUE IN THE N SEA WITH OCCASIONAL
GALES POSS
